This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama in December 2012, announcing the death of Senator Daniel K. Inouye, President pro tempore of the Senate. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in honor of Senator Inouye. It also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, consular offices, and military facilities abroad.